    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aa">
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="script" medium="ink"/>I woke to hear the lullaby<ref type="gloss_textual" target="i_woke_to_hear_the_lullaby_poem_glosses_textual.php#ARVEATCHAMOUNITITLE" /><add rend="linenumber-right-JR">520</add></l>
                    <l>Of the <del rend="strikethrough">fie</del> swift river rolling by</l>
                    <l>Monotonous yet beautiful</l>
                    <l>Ever <del rend="strikethrough"><unclear resp="#DCH">t</unclear></del> the gentle pebbly <del rend="strikethrough">swift</del> swell</l> 
                    <l><del rend="strikethrough">Of ever</del> And every ripple lent his plash</l>
                    <l>Joining in chorus wi<subst><del>f</del><add rend="overwriting">t</add></subst>h the dash <add rend="linenumber-right-JR">525</add></l>
                    <l>Of <del rend="strikethrough">m</del> every mighty mountain stream</l>
                    <l>That joyful sung his morning hymn</l>
                    <l>His iris glory round him quivering</l>
                    <l>Where his white showery falls were shivering</l>
                    <l>There is a melancholy smile<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">530</add></l>
                    <l>On natures features fair the while</l>
                    <l>When the dank dews descending grey,</l>
                    <l>Weep for the loss of parting day</l>
                    <l>There is a sad and soft complaining</l>
                    <l>In the light breeze when day is waning<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">535</add></l>
                    <l>The evening star is fair and full</l>
                    <l>But it is passing sorrowful<del rend="strikethrough">l</del></l>
                    <l>And merry is the laughing light</l>
                <pb facs="MSVIIIp55v"></pb>
                    <l>That blushes oer the heavens height</l>
                    <l>That stream and bird and <del rend="strikethrough"><unclear resp="#DCH">for</unclear></del> breeze and tree<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">540</add></l>
                    <l><del rend="strikethrough">V</del> For very joy sing merrily</l>
                    <l>When wakes the morn the morn the mountain snows</l>
                    <l>From their cold fixed pale repose</l>
                    <l>It was a most enchanting vision</l>
                    <l>The morning mists had upwards risen<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">545</add></l>
                    <l>And floating in the fields of air</l>
                    <l>Lay in long lines most calmly there</l>
                    <l>You could not call them clouds I wist</l>
                    <l>They were not smoke they were not mist</l>
                    <l>They were a sort of visible breeze,<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">550</add></l>
                    <l>Touching the tops of the pine trees</l>
                    <l>That as we passed beneath, and strook</l>
                    <l>Their stretchy branches ever shook</l>
                    <l>The laughing showers of <del rend="underline">lightso</del> dancing dew</l>
                    <l>Reflecting every rainbow hue<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">555</add></l>
                    <l>Or clinging to the clusters dank</l>
                    <l>of bright green moss upon the bank</l>
                    <l>And where those pines their crests had cloven</l>
                    <l>How rich the sun was interwoven</l>
                    <l>And smiling through the leafy shade<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">560</add></l>
                    <l>Among the spangled grass it played</l>
                    <l>And drank the dew from flower and blade</l>
                    <l>Melting the heavy drops to air</l>
                    <l>That so dragged down the gossamer</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
